5. COUNTING THE CONNECTIONS
======================================================================

Session S80 discoveries — connections found:

   1. Forbidden H = 7*3^k = I(K3 + kK1, 2)
      -> Tripling = adding isolated cycle to Omega

   2. 7 = |PG(2,2)| = Fano plane points
      -> First forbidden = smallest projective plane

   3. 21 = |PG(2,4)|, 63 = |PG(5,2)|
      -> Forbidden sequence = projective geometry points

   4. f(A_P) = 8I - 6A + J
      -> Tournament poly of Petersen = rank(E8)*I - h(G2)*A + J

   5. Petersen IS Ramanujan
      -> Ihara zeros on |u|=1/sqrt(KEY1)

   6. PSL(2,Z) = Z/KEY1 * Z/KEY2
      -> Modular group = free product of tournament keys

   7. N(f(omega)) = 91 = Phi3(2)*Phi3(3)
      -> Tournament poly norm at cube root = 7*13

   8. 504/240 = H_forb_2/V(Petersen)
      -> Eisenstein series ratio = forbidden/Petersen

   9. sigma_3(6) = 252 = C(10,5)
      -> E8 theta at h(G2) = middle binom of V(Petersen)

  10. 744 = |BT|*(h(E8)+1)
      -> j-invariant constant = 24*31

  11. Hamming [7,4,3] = [Phi3(KEY1), KEY1^2, KEY2]
      -> Perfect code from tournament keys

  12. Extended Golay [24,12,8] = [|BT|, h(E6), rank(E8)]
      -> Perfect code from Lie data

  13. S(5,8,24) = S(KEY1+KEY2, rank(E8), |BT|)
      -> Steiner system from tournament/Lie

  14. p(5) = 7 = H_forb_1
      -> Partition of KEY1+KEY2 = first forbidden

  15. p(9) = 30 = h(E8)
      -> Partition of KEY2^2 = E8 Coxeter

  16. p(11) = 56 = dim(V_E7) = f(10)
      -> Partition of 11 = tournament poly at V(P)

  17. p(18) = 385 = 5*7*11
      -> Partition of h(E7) = product of Ramanujan moduli

  18. C_4 = 14 = dim(G2)
      -> 4th Catalan = dimension of smallest exceptional

  19. C_5 = 42 = f(9) = 2*H_forb_2
      -> 5th Catalan = tournament polynomial of KEY2^2

  20. BT: 7 irreps = H_forb_1
      -> Binary tetrahedral irrep count = first forbidden

  21. BO: 8 irreps = rank(E8)
      -> Binary octahedral irrep count = rank(E8)

  22. BI: 9 irreps = KEY2^2
      -> Binary icosahedral irrep count = KEY2^2

  23. |GL(3,2)| = 168 = 7*24 = 8*21
      -> Fano automorphisms = H_forb_1*|BT| = rank(E8)*H_forb_2

  24. Pentagonal number differences = 3 = KEY2
      -> Euler's pentagonal theorem uses KEY2

  25. p(21) = 792 = C(12,5) = C(h(E6),5)
      -> Partition of H_forb_2 = binom of h(E6)

  26. Kissing: dim 1->2->3->4 gives 2->6->12->24
      -> Kissing numbers = KEY1, h(G2), h(E6), |BT|

  27. 1728 = 12^3 = h(E6)^3 = KEY1^6*KEY2^3
      -> Modular discriminant normalizer = Coxeter cube

TOTAL: 27 new cross-domain connections in session S80.

